off:n Turns the specified channel off. n = LC channel (1,2)
inv:n,v1 Sets up the specified channel to
output an invariant voltage v1.
n = LC channel (1,2)
v1 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
sin:n,v1,v2,t,ph<CR>
Sets up the specified channel to
output a sine wave varying
between v1 and v2, with period t
and phase ph.
n = LC channel (1,2)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
t  = 5-65535 milliseconds
ph = 0-360 (degrees)
saw:n,v1,v2,t,ph<CR>
Sets up the specified channel to
output a sawtooth wave varying
between v1 and v2, with period t
and phase ph.
n = LC channel (1,2)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
t  = 5-65535 milliseconds
ph = 0-360 (degrees)
tri:n,v1,v2,t,ph<CR>
Sets up the specified channel to
output a triangle wave varying
between v1 and v2, with period t
and phase ph.
n = LC channel (1,2)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
t  = 5-65535 milliseconds
ph = 0-360 (degrees)
sqr:n,v1,v2,t,ph,dc<CR>
Sets up the specified channel to
output a square wave varying
between v1 and v2, with period t,
phase ph, and duty cycle dc.
n = LC channel (1,2)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
t  = 5-65535 milliseconds
ph = 0-360 (degrees)
dc = 0-100 (percent)
tnew:n,v1,v2,t,ph,dc,tv,tt
<CR>
Sets up the specified channel to
output a square wave varying
between v1 and v2, with period t,
phase ph, duty cycle dc, with
pulses to TNE voltage tv, and of
duration TNE time tt.
n = LC channel (1,2)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
t  = 5-65535 milliseconds
ph = 0-360 (degrees)
dc =  0-100 (percent)
tv = 0-10000 (millivolts)
tt = 0-255 (milliseconds)
ext:n<CR>
Enables output channels to be
driven by signal applied to front
panel I/O connector.

n =channel (1,2)

thr:n,v1,v2<CR>
I/O connector n is monitored, and
if less than 2.5V, output = V1.
Otherwise, output is V2.
n = channel (1,2)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
trg:n,?<CR>
I/O connector n is monitored for
pulses.  When a pulse is received,
if the output is at V1, it switches
to V2.  If the output is at V2, it
switches to V1.
n = channel (1,2)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
wvf:n,?<CR>
Returns the current waveform
configuration.  All parameters are
returned regardless of waveform.
Some parameters will be
undefined for some waveforms.
Waveform parameter to
waveform conversion:
1 = invariant/off     2 = triangle
3 = sawtooth          4 = square
5 = TNE                 6 = sine
7 = external in        8 = threshold
9 = trigger.
Controller returns 9 parameters:
n = LC channel (1,2)
m = waveform (1-9)
v1,v2 = 0-10000 (millivolts)*
t  = 5-65535 (milliseconds)
ph = 0-360 (degrees)
dc =  0-100 (percent)
tv = 0-10000 (millivolts)
tt = 0-255 (milliseconds)
*- If the unit has the 20V option, the voltage becomes 20000mV.
