Table 3 – Temperature-Related ASCII commands for the D5020 controller
Firmware Command Description Notes
tmp:n,?<CR>
Query current temperature of
temperature controlled LC on
channel n.
Controller returns 16-bit integer i
converted to temperature by
T (ºC) = (i*500/65535) - 273.15
tsp:n,t<CR> Sets temperature setpoint for
temperature control for channel n
n = channel (1,2)
t is 16-bit integer
tsp:n,?<CR> Query current temperature
setpoint for channel n. Controller returns 16-bit integer (t)



Table 4 – Other ASCII commands for the D5020 controller
Firmware Command Description Notes
sync:n,ph,t<CR>
Produces sync pulses (high-low)
on front panel I/O connector
specified by n, with phase ph, and
time t.  This command will be
ignored if waveform is set to
external in, threshold or trigger,
as the I/O connector is already in
use for these waveforms.
n =channel (1,2)
ph = phase relative to waveform
(degrees)
t  = pulse length (microseconds)
tmp:n,?<CR>
Query current temperature of
temperature controlled LC on
channel n.
Controller returns 16-bit integer i
converted to temperature by
T (ºC) = (i*500/65535) - 273.15
tsp:n,t<CR> Sets temperature setpoint for
temperature control for channel n
n = channel (1,2)
t is 16-bit integer
tsp:n,?<CR> Query current temperature
setpoint for channel n. Controller returns 16-bit integer (t)
rsn:?<CR> Query controller’s serial number Controller returns serial number
string.
ver:?<CR> Query firmware version. Controller returns firmware version
and copyright string

